50|$|Judge <b>Robert</b> <b>Bork's</b> {{writings}} on antitrust law (particularly The Antitrust Paradox), {{along with those}} of Richard Posner and other law and economics thinkers, were heavily influential in causing a shift in the U.S. Supreme Court's approach to antitrust laws since the 1970s, to be focused solely on {{what is best for the}} consumer rather than the company's practices.|$|R
