50|$|AFJ {{played a}} role in the defeat of Ronald Reagan nominee <b>Robert</b> <b>Bork's</b> {{nomination}} to the Supreme Court of the United States in 1987. In 2001, the organization supported the nomination of Roger Gregory, a Bill Clinton nominee and the first African-American judge in the Fourth Circuit in 2001. In 2013, AFJ supported President Barack Obama's three nominees for the United States Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia Circuit.|$|R
